article.description: — Josh Cohen had 25 points in UMass' 91-77 victory against UMass-Lowell on Saturday.
article.headline: UMass defeats UMass-Lowell 91-77
article.story: AMHERST, Mass. -- — Josh Cohen had 25 points in UMass' 91-77 victory against UMass-Lowell on Saturday. Cohen also added 14 rebounds and four steals for the Minutemen (5-2). Rahsool Diggins scored 15 points and added six rebounds. Matt Cross had 14 points. Yuri Covington led the way for the River Hawks (6-3) with 14 points and two steals. Ayinde Hikim added 13 points, five assists and two steals for UMass-Lowell. Cam Morris III had 13 points. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
